WEBVTT

00:05.472 --> 00:06.573 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: Good
evening. I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:06.573 --> 00:08.909 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:08.909 --> 00:12.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: On the "NewsHour"
tonight, a deepening mystery:
What brought down a Russian
plane

00:12.746 --> 00:16.383 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in Egypt, killing
hundreds on board?

00:16.383 --> 00:22.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also ahead this
Monday: racial profiling in the
courtroom, how one case taken

00:22.256 --> 00:27.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the Supreme Court could
change the process of jury
selection nationwide.

00:27.261 --> 00:28.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHEN BRIGHT, President and
Senior Counsel, Southern Center
for Human Rights: In the
prosecutor's

00:28.695 --> 00:34.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
files, they had race-coded and
color-coded all the black people
in the list of the jurors.

00:34.601 --> 00:37.337 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
